org.rapla.client
Interface RaplaClientExtensionPoints

public interface RaplaClientExtensionPoints

Constant Pool of basic extension points of the Rapla client. You can add your extension in the provideService Method of your PluginDescriptor 

 container.addContainerProvidedComponent( REPLACE_WITH_EXTENSION_POINT_NAME, REPLACE_WITH_CLASS_IMPLEMENTING_EXTENSION, config);

See Also:
PluginDescriptor

CLIENT_EXTENSION

static final Class<ClientExtension> CLIENT_EXTENSION
A client extension is started automaticaly when a user has successfully login into the Rapla system. A class added as service doesn't need to implement a specific interface and is instanciated automaticaly after client login. You can add a RaplaContext parameter to your constructor to get access to the services of rapla.

PLUGIN_OPTION_PANEL_EXTENSION

static final TypedComponentRole<org.rapla.gui.internal.edit.PluginOptionPanel> PLUGIN_OPTION_PANEL_EXTENSION
You can add a specific configuration panel for your plugin. Note if you add a pluginOptionPanel you need to provide the PluginClass as hint. Example container.addContainerProvidedComponent( RaplaExtensionPoints.PLUGIN_OPTION_PANEL_EXTENSION, AutoExportPluginOption.class, getClass().getName());

See Also:
Preferences, OptionPanel
